# Packages to remove from the image after installation.
# Removed with `dnf remove` (tolerant of absence) in configure.sh.

# dracut-config-rescue generates a separate, large "rescue" initramfs + boot
# entry on the installed system. On a bootc/atomic desktop that's dead weight —
# recovery is a `bootc rollback` to the previous deployment, not a rescue kernel.
# Dropping it slims kernel updates and the image. (Recommended by the Fedora
# Magazine bootc-desktop guide.)
dracut-config-rescue

# openssh-server: this is a desktop device, not a remote-managed server, so we
# don't ship an SSH daemon. Removing the package also removes its units, so it
# can't be started even if something re-enables it. (openssh-clients stays for
# outbound ssh.)
openssh-server

# chromium
